Class PropagatorDependencyAdapter

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Adapter, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Adapter.Internal

    public abstract class PropagatorDependencyAdapter
extends PropagatorAbstractAdapter
    Listen to changes as mandated by some PropagatorFunctionAdapter(s).

    A PropagatorFunctionAdapter manages the state of a (several) data element(s) and listens to changes of some Notifier. When the state of the managed data elements must be refreshed as a function of changes of some other Notifier, then the PropagatorFunctionAdapter delegates the listening of those changes to a PropagatorDependencyAdapter, that must implement PropagatorAbstractAdapter.notifyChanged(org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notification) and call touch() appropriately.

    The PropagatorDependencyAdapter maintains a collection of PropagatorFunctionAdapters depending on this adapter.

    A PropagatorDependencyAdapter is created and added by calling PropagatorAbstractAdapter.addDependency(org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier, Object) on the depending adapter, passing the concrete type of to be created dependency adapter.

    A PropagatorDependencyAdapter is removed by calling PropagatorAbstractAdapter.removeDependency(org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier, Object) on the depending adapter, passing the concrete type of to be removed dependency adapter.
